# Project Conventions

- Use npm commands by default: `npm install`, `npm run dev`, `npm run build`.
- Prefer `npm run dev:light` for fast AI-assisted iteration.
- Use `npm run dev:host` in remote preview environments.
- Use `npm run dev:light:host` in remote preview environments when speed matters.
- Run `npm run doctor` before deeper debugging in a fresh environment.
- Use `npm run routes` and `npm run map` to orient yourself before broad edits.
- Use `npm run clean` only for generated build/cache output.
- Do not manually edit `src/routeTree.gen.ts` unless regenerating route metadata is impossible.
- Keep environment values in `.env`; use `.env.example` as the template.
- Prefer existing components in `src/components/ui` and helpers in `src/lib`.
- Main files: `src/routes/__root.tsx`, `src/pages/Login.tsx`, `src/lib/authContext.tsx`.
